[1] Cholera - Uganda (Arua)
Date: Fri 21 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Monitor (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200607210248.html>

Cholera hit the densely populated Kenya Ward of River Oli division
last week, killing at least one resident of the Municipality on Mon
17 Jul 2006. Two other victims were taken for treatment at Oli Health
Center and have been discharged according to the town Health
Inspector, Ms Norah Fuathum.
The Daily Monitor has learned that the cholera inpatients came from
the same family, while the deceased was their neighbor.
Mr Charles Asiki, the mayor, who recently won the mayoral race on a
pledge to clean up the town and eliminate occurrence of communicable
diseases, said he was embarrassed by the cholera resurgence because
it comes as a result of improper hygiene.
The mayor said the problem started in the premises of a landlord with
19 tenants and over 100 family members, all using a single latrine.
[Byline: Tabu Butagira]
--
