[2] Cholera - Uganda (Gulu, Pader)
Date: Fri 14 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: New Vision [edited]
<http://www.newvision.co.ug/detail.php?mainNewsCategoryId=8&newsCategoryId=16&newsId=509392>

At least 24 cases of cholera have been registered in Gulu district,
following the disease outbreak in the district 2 weeks ago.
The WHO distribution sheet on the disease from 21 Jun to 5 Jul 2006
presented at a Municipal Cholera task force meeting showed that one
case of the disease was also registered in Lacekocot in Pader district.
The sheet revealed that 7 cases were registered at Unyama IDP camp in
Paicho sub-county, Gulu district, 6 from Layibi division, 5 from
Bibia in Atiak sub- county, 3 from Bardege division, one each from
Pece division and Patiko sub-county.
[Byline: Cornes Lubangakene]
--
