[3] Cholera, diarrhea - India (Gujarat)
Date: Wed 19 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Hindu [edited]
<http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/002200607191135.htm>

Five days after the district authorities declared Chhani Nagarpalika
as cholera- hit, 18 more people had tested positive for , as scores
of others were treated for gastroenteritis and diarrhea in different
hospitals in the city. Admitting that the number of cholera positive
cases had increased to 27 during the past week, Chief District Health
Officer (CDHO) Dr Bhagwat Etare said 5 more people were admitted to
the hospital with similar symptoms yesterday, 18 Jul 2006. The fluid
samples were collected for testing.
Although there was no report of any casualty due to the outbreak of
cholera, the disease had spread panic in Chhani and its neighboring
villages, as hundreds of people, including women and children, had
reportedly suffered from water-borne diseases during the last fortnight.
Sources in the CDHO office said about 90 patients were still admitted
to Chhani PHC, SSG and other hospitals in the city.
